cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper presents an information-theoretic framework for sequential adaptive compressed sensing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses algorithms for Gaussian and Gaussian Mixture Model signals, which are commonly used in machine learning.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper connects compressed sensing and blackbox complexity of sequential query algorithms.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses numerical examples using simulated and real data.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms using numerical examples.
